### Cisco IOS
### Pings

ping <MikroTik-OSPF-IP> source <local-OSPF-intf-IP> repeat 20
show arp | include <MikroTik-IP>
show mac address-table interface <facing-intf>          # if L2 switch involved

### OSPF Neighbor & Adjacency Status (Most Important Commands)

show ip ospf neighbor                                   # neighbor table + state
show ip ospf neighbor detail                            # timers, MTU, options, auth, priority
show ip ospf interface brief                            # quick interface overview
show ip ospf interface <intf>                           # detailed: hello/dead, network type, cost, MTU
show ip ospf                                            # global: router-id, areas, process, ref bandwidth

### OSPF Routes & Database

show ip route ospf                                      # only OSPF routes
show ip ospf database                                   # LSDB summary
show ip ospf database router                            # detailed router (Type-1) LSAs
show ip ospf database external                          # external (Type-5) if redistribution

### Logging & Real-Time Debugging

show logging | include OSPF
debug ip ospf hello
debug ip ospf adj
debug ip ospf events
debug ip ospf packet                                    # verbose – use ACL to filter if needed
undebug all                                             # stop debugs!
terminal monitor                                        # see debugs in SSH/console

### Quick Resets (When Stuck – Use Carefully!)

clear ip ospf process                                   # full reset (all adjacencies drop!)
clear ip ospf neighbor <neighbor-IP>                    # targeted clear

### Firewall / Protocol Allows (Don't Forget!)

access-list 100 permit ospf any any
